======================================================================
DIVERSITY NOTE — Query 1 output explained
======================================================================

  #1 and #2 both show "Snowy Holiday Nights" — are these siblings?

  DB check:
    gen_id 28c227c6 → Snowy Holiday Nights path_number=1 (song_id 3db6dde6)
    gen_id 29d8590d → Snowy Holiday Nights path_number=1 (song_id 6c024000)

  Different generation_ids → two separate source records that happen to share
  a title. Not siblings. diversify_results correctly allows both.

  A real diversity violation would be path_number=1 AND path_number=2 from the
  SAME generation_id appearing together. The query filters path_number=1 only,
  so siblings are excluded from this verification query by design.

  In normal search flow (no path_number filter), diversify_results enforces
  max 1 song per generation_id in the top 5 — that is where Part 5 fires.
